            . I am shopman to Mr. Collier, he lives in <placeName id="t18170917-99-crimeloc489">Lamb's-conduit-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-99-crimeloc489" type="placeName" value="Lamb's-conduit-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-99-crimeloc489" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-99-off487 t18170917-99-crimeloc489"></join>. On the 1st of August, about eight o'clock in the evening, the prisoner came into the shop, and asked to look at some black silk handkerchiefs she unfolded two pieces, and spread them over the others; she drew one of the folded pieces from under them, put it under her shawl, said they would not do, and went out. I followed her, and brought her back she immediately dropped them; I gave her in charge. They are worth 40s.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 18.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18170917-99-verdict490" type="verdictDescription">
